{{Talk:Battle of Flores (1592)/GA1}}
== Can we clarify this? ==
"George Clifford, the Earl of Cumberland had a large stake in the expedition; the ship Dainty (owned by John Hawkins) under command of John Norton as well as many of the support ships that were with the fleet belonged to him."
So who owned Dainty? Clifford or Hawkins? Or does "belonging to" mean something different from "owned by" that, not being versed in naval terms, I don't know about? [[User:MostRecentUser|MostRecentUser]] ([[User talk:MostRecentUser|talk]]) 16:51, 14 February 2014 (UTC) :As it was a joint stock venture, Hawkins still owned the ship, but the fleet belonged to Cumberland; complicated yes but this was how things operated in Elizabethan England.[[User:ChristiaandeWet|ChrisWet]] ([[User talk:ChristiaandeWet|talk]]) 19:29, 14 February 2014 (UTC)
